-- Credit Suisse doubles its litigation provisions
-- 
-- Thu Apr 03, 2014 01:35AM EDT
-- None



ZURICH, April 3 (Reuters) - Credit Suisse <CSGN.VX> has doubled its litigation provisions as it increased the funds it has set aside to settle an ongoing U.S. tax probe and avoid prosecution for helping Americans evade taxes.

Switzerland's second-biggest bank said in its annual report  published on Thursday that it has 2.33 billion Swiss francs ($2.63 billion) in litigation provisions compared to 1.16 billion a year earlier.